        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 23 at 4:44PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 444 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mattawan, or 7 miles northeast of Paw Paw, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kalamazoo...           Portage...             Vicksburg...
Parchment...           Comstock Northwest...  Westwood...
Kendall...             Comstock...            Oshtemo...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
